An Act relative to locating missing persons via mobile data (Kelsey's Bill).
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 6A of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting at the end thereof the
2 following new section:—
3 Section 18M.
4 (a) As used in this section the term “Executive office” shall mean the executive office of
5 public safety and security.
6 (b) Upon request of a law enforcement agency, a wireless telecommunications carrier or
7 in-vehicle security and communications service provider, shall immediately provide location
8 information concerning the telecommunications devices of the user to the requesting law
9 enforcement agency (i) in order to respond to a call for emergency services initiated from the
1 of 2

10 telecommunications devices of the user, (ii) to assist in a missing person investigation, or (iii) in
11 `an emergency situation that involves the risk of death or serious physical harm. Nothing in this
12 section shall prohibit a wireless telecommunications carrier from establishing protocols by which
13 the carrier could voluntarily disclose location information.
14 (c) (1) All wireless carriers and in-vehicle security and communications service providers
15 shall submit their emergency contact information to the executive office in order to facilitate
16 requests from a public safety department for location information in accordance with subsection
17 (b). Such contact information shall be submitted annually by June 15th or immediately upon any
18 change in contact information.
19 (d) No cause of action shall lie in any court against any wireless telecommunications
20 carrier or in-vehicle security and communications service provider, its officers, employees,
21 agents or other specified persons for providing call location information while acting in good
22 faith and in accordance with the provisions of this section.
23 (e) The executive office shall maintain a database containing emergency contact
24 information for all wireless telecommunications carriers and in-vehicle security and
25 communications service providers and shall make the information immediately available upon
26 request to all public safety answer points in the state. The executive office shall promulgate
27 regulations for administration and enforcement of this section; provided further, that such
28 regulations shall be promulgated no later than December 31, 2023.
